Messing around on my guitar over the holidays put me in a nostalgic mood. Reflecting on 2022 I am in awe of the treasures it gave me and lessons it taught me. So many lessons. In the end, my heart is smiling. 

I was writing about how I can be better next year. To be kinder, wiser, more focused. To spend more time with my instruments / in nature. 

Then I was writing reflections of the past year. In 2022, I played my first @coachella, I fell in love with Ibiza at @house_of_frequency and played my first summer residency with @storytellersibiza , traveled all over Europe playing music and meeting the coolest people, released my first track on @thehigherground with my bestie @fedele , finished even more that are coming out next year (!!!!!), began learning how to sing with @mtchllrose , signed with @threesixzero and @liaisonartists , moved to Miami and built my dream little home studio (last photo 🤓), discovered how much I absolutely love breathwork / meditation and hanging out with Ableton all day, met someone who changed my life, and laughed a lot with my peoples. 

Even just writing this motivates me for what’s coming. My favorite part of 2023 so far is the potential of emptiness 🌬❤️‍🔥

Nothing would be possible alone either. Sending out all my love to the people in my life who were there for the ups and the downs !! Especially you @alex_perez_tm 🫶🏼🫶🏼🫶🏼
My New Years resolution is to make friends with making reels 🤣 here’s to 2022 and wishing all of us the best year yet in 2023 ❤️‍🔥❤️‍🔥❤️‍🔥

Wow it’s already February 1st … January was a wild one ⚡️⚡️ I rang in the new year with the ones I love the most here at home, then I had shows in Colombia, Costa Rica, Miami, NYC and back to Miami. I finished another new track I’m dying to share, moved into a new apartment, fell in love with a monkey and started a journaling course with daily writing prompts. Hoping this will expedite all my dreams into reality 😬

I appreciate all of the beautiful memories and can’t wait to see what February has in store 💥 I’m taking two weeks off to hang out with bAbleton and then I’ll be in LA - hosting a badass sound meditation journey if you’re in town and feeling the call - and then I’m off to Athens and Brussels at the end of the month for some exciting shows. 

PS : I hope you guys enjoy this reel, I’m getting better but it still takes me a few hours and a lot of slow breathing to get past the anxiety making reels gives me 😅❤️❤️❤️

@coleknight is the very definition of self-taught. 

Born in the U.S., she began her career as a model before leaving the catwalk for the DJ booth. 

Her style is an ethereal blend of melodic techno, electro grooves, glittery disco and deep tribal rhythms - an intrinsic mix of her love for spirituality with a meditative aspect to her sets at Coachella, Burning Man or even We Can Dance bringing light everywhere.

I’m from a small town in Illinois, and never did I think I’d be a DJ growing up. I’ve never seen my parents drink or go to parties and my brothers and I haven’t all been together aside from Christmas in years. When I got booked to play @summercampfest , a festival that’s been around for 22+ years in Illinois, I was stoked - I remember growing up the cool kids in my hometown ones got to go. I always wanted to go, and finally I made it 😉 but the best part for me was that my whole family came with me, even my 87 year old grandpa drove all the way from Missouri to rave with us.  I’ll never forget being on stage playing some crazy music and seeing my mom, my dad, my brothers and @lucazawesome dancing up there with me, and my grandpa on the grass in the lawn chair that he brought for himself drinking his beer. I feel like the luckiest creature in the world… it’s the truth that music can bring people together ❤️🥹❤️

I’m still trying to determine if last weeks adventure actually happened… @lucazawesome and I hiked 14,000 ft up a mountain with a view of an active volcano and camped overnight. We hiked up to the summit at 4am to make it to the most beautiful sunrise I’ve ever seen, in freezing weather ! It was honestly the first time my brain has gone totally still. At one point my only thought was “left, right, left, right” trying to keep my feet working. When we made it back down we headed to Lake Aititlan for a couple days of recovery. I made some music and discovered a new obsession for cacao drinks and Lucas droned every location… Or was that all a dream?
